  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.66\r\nOS & Version: Windows10 64/ntfs hdd toshiba 7.2k rpm, 1tb\r\nchaindata folder symlinked to a secondary hdd since my primary drive is a 120 GB SSD with not enough space. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nBlockchain files (.ldb) unfragmented.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nEvery ~2 MB .ldb file has is divided to at least 5 fragments, the most fragmented ones divided to 20 fragments. Leading to horrible disc performance (usage 100%, read write 2-4 MB/s).  (Checked with Piriform Defraggler). \r\n\r\nWhat can i do to augment this situation?",
